<#GAPDoc Label="IsGreensClassOfPartialPermSemigp">
<ManSection>
  <Prop Name="IsGreensClassOfPartialPermSemigp" Arg="obj"/>
  <Returns><K>true</K> or <K>false</K>.</Returns>
  <Description>
    <C>IsGreensClassOfPartialPermSemigp</C> return <K>true</K> if the object
    <A>obj</A> is a Green's class of a semigroup of partial permutations and
    <K>false</K> if it is not. <P/>

    This property is required so that a Green's class knows that it belongs to 
    a semigroup of partial permutations, so that the methods defined in the
    &Citrus; are used in preference to those in the library.
    <Example>gap> S:=InverseSemigroup( PartialPermNC( [ 1, 3 ], [ 4, 3 ] ),
> PartialPermNC( [ 1, 2, 3 ], [ 4, 1, 2 ] ) );;
gap> D:=GreensDClassOfElement(S, PartialPermNC( [ 1, 3 ], [ 4, 3 ] ) );        
{&lt;identity on [ 1, 3 ]>}
gap> IsGreensClassOfPartPermSemigroup(D);
true</Example>
  </Description>
</ManSection>
<#/GAPDoc>

<#GAPDoc Label="DomainOfPartialPermSemigroup">
<ManSection>
  <Oper Name="DomainOfPartialPermSemigroup" Arg="S"/>
  <Oper Name="Points" Arg="S" Label="for a semigroup of partial perms"/>
  <Oper Name="Points" Arg="C" Label="for a partial perm coll"/>
  <Returns>a set of positive integers.</Returns>
  <Description>
    <C>Points</C> returns the points acted on by the semigroup of partial
    permutations <A>S</A> or the partial permutation collection <A>C</A>,
    respectively. See also <Ref Oper="MovedPoints" Label="for a partial perm"/>.
    <P/>

    <C>DomainOfPartialPermSemigroup</C> is a synonym of <C>Points</C>. 

    <Example>
gap> S:=InverseSemigroup( PartialPermNC( [ 1, 2, 3 ], [ 1, 3, 2 ] ),
> PartialPermNC( [ 1, 2, 3 ], [ 1, 2, 20 ] ) );;
gap> MovedPoints(S);
[ 2, 3, 20 ]
gap> Points(S);
[ 1, 2, 3, 20 ]</Example>
  </Description>
</ManSection>
<#/GAPDoc>

<#GAPDoc Label="GeneratorsOfInverseSemigroup">
<ManSection>
  <Attr Name="GeneratorsOfInverseSemigroup" Arg="S"/>
  <Returns>a list of partial permutations.</Returns>
  <Description>
    If <A>S</A> is an inverse semigroup of partial permutations, then
    <C>GeneratorsOfInverseSemigroup</C> returns the list of partial
    permutations used to define <A>S</A>, that is, an inverse semigroup
    generating set for <A>S</A>. Note that <A>S</A> is then the semigroup
    generated by the partial permutations in 
    <C>GeneratorsOfInverseSemigroup(<A>S</A>)</C> and their inverses.
    <P/>

    If <A>S</A> is an inverse monoid, then <C>GeneratorsOfInverseSemigroup</C>
    returns the list of partial permutations used to define <A>S</A> (as
    described above) and the identity of <A>S</A>; see <Ref Meth="One"
      Label="for a partial perm"/>. <P/>

    See also <Ref Func="InverseSemigroup"/> and <Ref Func="Generators"/>.

    <Example>
gap> S:=InverseMonoid(
>  PartialPermNC( [ 1, 2 ], [ 1, 4 ] ),
>  PartialPermNC( [ 1, 2, 4 ], [ 3, 4, 1 ] ) );;
gap> GeneratorsOfSemigroup(S);
[ &lt;identity on [ 1 .. 4 ]>, [ 1, 2 ] -> [ 1, 4 ], [ 1, 2, 4 ] -> [ 3, 4, 1 ], 
  [ 1, 4 ] -> [ 1, 2 ], [ 1, 3, 4 ] -> [ 4, 1, 2 ] ]
gap> GeneratorsOfInverseSemigroup(S);
[ &lt;identity on [ 1 .. 4 ]>, [ 1, 2 ] -> [ 1, 4 ], [ 1, 2, 4 ] -> [ 3, 4, 1 ] ]
gap> GeneratorsOfMonoid(S);
[ [ 1, 2 ] -> [ 1, 4 ], [ 1, 2, 4 ] -> [ 3, 4, 1 ], [ 1, 4 ] -> [ 1, 2 ], 
  [ 1, 3, 4 ] -> [ 4, 1, 2 ] ]</Example>
  </Description>
</ManSection>
<#/GAPDoc>

<#GAPDoc Label="GeneratorsOfInverseMonoid">
<ManSection>
  <Attr Name="GeneratorsOfInverseMonoid" Arg="S"/>
  <Returns>a list of partial permutations.</Returns>
  <Description>
    If <A>S</A> is an inverse monoid of partial permutations, then
    <C>GeneratorsOfInverseMonoid</C> returns the list of partial
    permutations used to define <A>S</A>, that is, an inverse monoid
    generating set for <A>S</A>. Note that <A>S</A> is then the semigroup
    generated by the partial permutations in 
    <C>GeneratorsOfInverseSemigroup(<A>S</A>)</C>, their inverses, and the
    identity of <A>S</A>; see <Ref Meth="One" Label="for a partial perm"/>.

    See also <Ref Func="InverseMonoid"/> and <Ref Func="Generators"/>.

    <Example>
gap> S:=InverseMonoid(
>  PartialPermNC( [ 1, 2 ], [ 1, 4 ] ),
>  PartialPermNC( [ 1, 2, 4 ], [ 3, 4, 1 ] ) );;
gap> GeneratorsOfInverseMonoid(S);
[ [ 1, 2 ] -> [ 1, 4 ], [ 1, 2, 4 ] -> [ 3, 4, 1 ] ]</Example>
  </Description>
</ManSection>
<#/GAPDoc>


